Pan-Seared New York Steak with Mushroom Bordelaise

$45.99
850 kcal
Difficulty: 75%

Allergens:

DairyMushrooms

Dietary Tags:

Gluten-FreeHigh-ProteinLow-Carb

Tags:

SteakGourmetComfort FoodElegant Dinner

Description

A classic steak dish featuring a succulent New York steak topped with a rich mushroom bordelaise, served with creamy polenta and crispy Brussels sprouts.

Ingredients

  • New York Strip Steak: 2 (8 oz each)
  • Butter: 4 tbsp
  • Shallots: 2, finely chopped
  • Cremini Mushrooms: 1 cup, sliced
  • Red Wine: 1 cup
  • Beef Stock: 1 cup
  • Fresh Thyme: 1 tbsp, chopped
  • Polenta: 1 cup
  • Heavy Cream: 1/2 cup
  • Parmesan Cheese: 1/4 cup, grated
  • Brussels Sprouts: 1 lb, halved
  • Pancetta: 4 oz, diced
  • Aged Cheddar: 1 cup, shredded
  • Baking Powder: 2 tsp
  • Flour: 2 cups
